01:09:47,131 --> 01:09:51,409
- What's Jep's floozy friend wearing?
- I don't know.

730
01:09:51,571 --> 01:09:54,722
Jep's proving to be
a disappointment.

731
01:09:54,891 --> 01:09:57,928
- Good evening, countess.
- Hello, you're looking well.

732
01:09:58,131 --> 01:10:02,329
I wish I could say that same
about the count. Hello, ladies!

733
01:10:02,731 --> 01:10:05,609
Are you stupid?
You're distracting my artist.

734
01:10:05,731 --> 01:10:07,130
Dad, we're having fun.

735
01:10:07,331 --> 01:10:09,765
Carmelina, come and do some work.

736
01:10:09,891 --> 01:10:11,688
Mom, I want to play here.

737
01:10:11,811 --> 01:10:14,883
- Has this human being gone mad?
- We'll sort it out.

738
01:10:15,051 --> 01:10:18,248
- I'm not coming, I'm staying here.
- You don't mean that.

739
01:10:18,371 --> 01:10:20,566
Europe's greatest gallery owners
are outside.

740
01:10:20,691 --> 01:10:24,479
If you show them what you can do
then ours will be a happy family.

741
01:10:24,611 --> 01:10:27,364
But I'm already happy,
I want to be a vet one day.

742
01:10:27,531 --> 01:10:32,400
Get to bed, you two!
My kids are going to bed.

743
01:10:32,571 --> 01:10:33,481
Come.

744
01:10:33,611 --> 01:10:36,045
I'll go to bed too.
I'm a kid too.

745
01:10:41,051 --> 01:10:43,326
She blushes and says:

746
01:10:43,531 --> 01:10:47,683
"Forgive me, I didn't know
you loved me so much.

747
01:10:48,091 --> 01:10:51,049
My ignorance is obscene."

748
01:10:51,531 --> 01:10:53,761
He looks at her, reassuringly,
and says:

749
01:10:53,971 --> 01:10:57,168
"Let me defend our love".

750
01:10:57,331 --> 01:11:00,050
How's that for the start
of the second act?

751
01:11:00,171 --> 01:11:02,162
You've written a pile of shit.

752
01:13:52,811 --> 01:13:54,722
That girl was crying.

753
01:13:54,811 --> 01:13:57,484
Nonsense!
That girl earns millions!

754
01:13:58,611 --> 01:14:00,442
Excuse me a moment.

755
01:14:03,371 --> 01:14:06,249
- Hi, Stefano.
- Hi.

756
01:14:06,891 --> 01:14:10,566
- The catering's gone downhill.
- Rome's gone downhill.

757
01:14:10,651 --> 01:14:12,050
Steeply downhill!

758
01:14:15,531 --> 01:14:17,681
Do you have the case with you?

759
01:14:20,411 --> 01:14:22,925
- I always do.
- You up for it?

760
01:15:27,211 --> 01:15:28,246
See that?

761
01:15:33,371 --> 01:15:37,603
Stefano has the keys to Rome's
most beautiful buildings.

762
01:15:39,211 --> 01:15:40,724
Is he a doorman?

763
01:15:42,491 --> 01:15:44,766
No, he's not a doorman.

764
01:15:45,091 --> 01:15:47,525
He's friends with princesses.

765
01:15:50,571 --> 01:15:51,924
Are you ready?

766
01:15:52,891 --> 01:15:54,290
Come with me.

767
01:17:54,131 --> 01:17:56,326
Good evening, Princesses.

768
01:17:56,451 --> 01:17:58,601
Good evening.

769
01:18:11,331 --> 01:18:13,083
How come you have all these keys?

770
01:18:15,011 --> 01:18:16,649
Because...

771
01:18:18,171 --> 01:18:20,002
I'm a trustworthy person.

772
01:18:34,971 --> 01:18:39,169
Did you see? It looked huge,
but it's tiny.

773
01:18:40,851 --> 01:18:44,048
Stay still, I'll take a photo of you.
Don't move.

774
01:18:47,611 --> 01:18:49,886
That's no good.
Laugh.

775
01:18:52,211 --> 01:18:53,690
Got it?

776
01:18:54,091 --> 01:18:56,241
Yes, that's good.

777
01:19:47,571 --> 01:19:50,529
Many think that a funeral,

778
01:19:50,651 --> 01:19:53,802
is a fortuitous event,
without any rules.

779
01:19:54,491 --> 01:19:55,970
That's not true.

780
01:19:56,491 --> 01:20:00,166
A funeral is a high-society event
par excellence.

781
01:20:01,651 --> 01:20:04,927
You must never forget
that at a funeral

782
01:20:05,771 --> 01:20:07,887
you are appearing on stage.

783
01:20:12,131 --> 01:20:13,610
Nice.

784
01:20:14,531 --> 01:20:16,169
Nice, but try the other one.

785
01:20:18,051 --> 01:20:22,920
You must patiently wait
for the relatives to disperse.

786
01:20:23,411 --> 01:20:28,280
Once you are sure
that all the guests are seated...

787
01:20:28,491 --> 01:20:32,120
only at that point, may you offer
your condolences to the family.

788
01:20:32,651 --> 01:20:36,564
In this way, everyone will see you.

789
01:20:36,811 --> 01:20:39,200
You take the mourner's hands,

790
01:20:39,371 --> 01:20:43,000
and rest yours on their arms.

791
01:20:43,411 --> 01:20:47,040
You whisper something to them,
a comforting phrase,

792
01:20:47,251 --> 01:20:49,242
said with authority.

793
01:20:49,371 --> 01:20:51,726
For example:

794
01:20:51,851 --> 01:20:56,447
"In the days to come,
when you feel the void,

795
01:20:57,131 --> 01:21:01,568
I want you to know
that you can always count on me."

796
01:21:03,051 --> 01:21:04,928
The public will ask...

797
01:21:06,571 --> 01:21:09,449
"What's Jep Gambardella saying?"

798
01:21:22,131 --> 01:21:24,122
This is definitely the right dress.

799
01:21:29,211 --> 01:21:33,648
You're allowed to retire
to a corner by yourself,

800
01:21:34,131 --> 01:21:37,328
as if contemplating your sorrow.

801
01:21:38,731 --> 01:21:43,202
However, another matter
must be approached with shrewdness.

802
01:21:43,891 --> 01:21:48,282
The chosen place needs
to be isolated

803
01:21:48,411 --> 01:21:50,447
but clearly visible
to the public.

804
01:21:51,171 --> 01:21:57,280
Besides, a performance is good when
it is devoid of any superfluity.

805
01:21:59,651 --> 01:22:01,403
So, the fundamental rule:

806
01:22:03,011 --> 01:22:05,400
One must never cry at a funeral.

807
01:22:06,531 --> 01:22:09,523
You must never steal the show
from the family's sorrow.

808
01:22:09,651 --> 01:22:12,723
That is forbidden.

809
01:22:15,651 --> 01:22:17,403
Because it is immoral.

810
01:22:54,011 --> 01:22:55,683
Viola.

811
01:23:04,011 --> 01:23:08,527
In the days to come,
when you feel the void,

812
01:23:09,771 --> 01:23:12,046
you can always count on me.

813
01:24:00,171 --> 01:24:05,689
Now I ask Andrea's friends
to come forward,

814
01:24:07,571 --> 01:24:10,404
so that the coffin
may be carried outside.

815
01:24:31,931 --> 01:24:33,000
Your back!

816
01:25:41,891 --> 01:25:44,166
It was nice not making love.

817
01:25:45,931 --> 01:25:47,808
It was nice loving each other.

818
01:25:48,611 --> 01:25:52,240
I'd forgotten what loving someone
was about, I'd forgotten that.

819
01:25:58,971 --> 01:26:01,531
I spend all my money to cure myself.

820
01:26:10,291 --> 01:26:12,282
Your breakfast.

821
01:26:13,371 --> 01:26:16,408
Come on, I'm taking you to see
a sea monster today.

822
01:26:37,251 --> 01:26:38,764
Your breakfast.

823
01:26:40,931 --> 01:26:42,922
Five more minutes.

824
01:26:49,771 --> 01:26:51,807
Can you see the sea?

825
01:26:58,571 --> 01:27:00,289
Where?

826
01:27:00,451 --> 01:27:02,123
On the ceiling.

827
01:27:08,211 --> 01:27:10,247
Yes, I can see it.

828
01:28:40,891 --> 01:28:43,644
Who's going to look after you now?

829
01:28:58,011 --> 01:29:01,924
I'm sorry about your daughter.
My condolences.

830
01:29:27,291 --> 01:29:33,048
I spent all my summers
making plans for September.

831
01:29:33,171 --> 01:29:34,763
Not any longer.

832
01:29:36,211 --> 01:29:40,329
Now I spend the summer
remembering the good intentions

833
01:29:40,851 --> 01:29:42,762
which vanished.

834
01:29:43,331 --> 01:29:47,210
In part because of laziness,
in part because of carelessness.

835
01:29:50,411 --> 01:29:53,244
What's wrong
with feeling nostalgic?

836
01:29:54,771 --> 01:29:56,841
It's the only distraction left for those

837
01:29:56,971 --> 01:29:59,485
who've no faith in the future!

838
01:30:03,131 --> 01:30:04,928
Without rain...

839
01:30:05,371 --> 01:30:09,762
August is coming to an end
and September isn't arriving.

840
01:30:11,131 --> 01:30:13,440
And I'm so ordinary!

841
01:30:14,131 --> 01:30:16,440
But there's no need to worry.

842
01:30:16,851 --> 01:30:19,809
It's all right, it's okay.

843
01:30:27,331 --> 01:30:28,730
Bravo!

844
01:30:43,931 --> 01:30:45,284
Thank you.

845
01:31:30,891 --> 01:31:33,246
What are you doing here?

846
01:31:34,131 --> 01:31:37,521
Arturo!
Why are you here?

847
01:31:37,691 --> 01:31:41,001
Don't you see?
I'm rehearsing my magic show.

848
01:31:41,131 --> 01:31:45,090
This is tomorrow's special number:
The vanishing giraffe.

849
01:31:45,851 --> 01:31:47,569
You can make this giraffe vanish?

850
01:31:47,691 --> 01:31:50,649
Of course I can make
the giraffe vanish!

851
01:31:52,171 --> 01:31:54,560
Then make me vanish too.

852
01:31:56,011 --> 01:32:01,722
Jep, do you think that if I could
really make people vanish

853
01:32:02,131 --> 01:32:05,965
I'd still be here at my age
playing these circus games?

854
01:32:07,211 --> 01:32:08,769
It's just a trick.

855
01:32:13,091 --> 01:32:14,729
It's just a trick!

856
01:32:24,131 --> 01:32:26,087
Romano, how did it go?

857
01:32:26,331 --> 01:32:28,242
Well, they clapped.

858
01:32:28,571 --> 01:32:30,323
I'm glad.

859
01:32:30,651 --> 01:32:33,324
- So why are you so sad?
- I'm not sad.

860
01:32:33,611 --> 01:32:35,124
What's with the giraffe?

861
01:32:35,291 --> 01:32:38,044
For a magic show.
I'll come and see you tomorrow.

862
01:32:38,211 --> 01:32:40,042
I'm not doing the show tomorrow.

863
01:32:40,931 --> 01:32:42,603
Why not? You said it went well.

864
01:32:42,731 --> 01:32:47,486
I'm leaving, I'm going back
to my home town, for good.

865
01:32:47,731 --> 01:32:51,201
I won't even pack up my things,
I'll leave it all.

866
01:32:53,571 --> 01:32:56,847
I've lived in this city
for 40 years.

867
01:32:57,651 --> 01:32:59,846
And in the end I thought...

868
01:33:01,371 --> 01:33:04,044
the only person
who deserved a goodbye

869
01:33:04,451 --> 01:33:06,282
was you.

870
01:33:08,291 --> 01:33:10,361
So you're leaving?

871
01:33:12,611 --> 01:33:15,523
Romano... why are you leaving?

872
01:33:16,011 --> 01:33:18,445
Rome has really disappointed me.

873
01:33:24,051 --> 01:33:25,689
Bye, Jep.

874
01:33:44,931 --> 01:33:46,489
See?

875
01:34:14,891 --> 01:34:17,928
- Want some coffee?
- No, thanks. I know you're busy.

876
01:34:18,091 --> 01:34:19,763
I need to ask you something.

877
01:34:20,291 --> 01:34:21,770
Go ahead.

878
01:34:25,891 --> 01:34:28,166
Why did Elisa leave me?

879
01:34:31,251 --> 01:34:32,923
I don't know.

880
01:34:33,051 --> 01:34:36,930
Didn't she say anything about it
in her diary?

881
01:34:37,531 --> 01:34:39,601
No, I don't think so.

882
01:34:42,611 --> 01:34:46,320
Would you be offended
if I asked to read it?

883
01:34:46,491 --> 01:34:49,164
No, I wouldn't.

884
01:34:49,771 --> 01:34:52,046
In fact, I'd understand.

885
01:34:53,811 --> 01:34:56,086
But I'm afraid I can't
let you read it.

886
01:34:56,251 --> 01:34:57,240
Why not?

887
01:34:58,211 --> 01:35:00,930
Because a few days after the
funeral, I threw it away.

888
01:35:06,531 --> 01:35:08,601
May I introduce you
to my girlfriend?

889
01:35:10,091 --> 01:35:12,400
Hello, my name's Polina.

890
01:35:15,411 --> 01:35:18,050
Like Polina in "The Gambler"
by Dostoyevsky.

891
01:35:24,131 --> 01:35:25,962
What are you doing tonight?

892
01:35:27,691 --> 01:35:29,568
Nothing.

893
01:35:30,131 --> 01:35:32,008
Polina's going to finish ironing...

894
01:35:32,891 --> 01:35:35,121
then we'll drink a glass
of red wine.

895
01:35:35,851 --> 01:35:39,446
We'll watch some television
and go to bed.

896
01:35:40,611 --> 01:35:41,566
What about you?

897
01:35:43,211 --> 01:35:47,682
I'll have a lot of drinks, but not
so many as to become unruly.

898
01:35:48,491 --> 01:35:50,607
And then...

899
01:35:51,611 --> 01:35:56,002
when you'll be getting up
I'll be going to bed.

900
01:36:02,651 --> 01:36:05,802
What lovely people you are!

901
01:36:15,811 --> 01:36:17,881
I love doing the train!

902
01:36:22,251 --> 01:36:23,730
I'll screw you.

903
01:36:26,091 --> 01:36:28,082
"Who am I?"

904
01:36:29,731 --> 01:36:32,768
That's how
one of Breton's novels began.

905
01:36:33,651 --> 01:36:36,723
And of course in the book
there's no reply.

906
01:36:37,731 --> 01:36:40,040
- Did you hear about Viola?
- What?

907
01:36:40,251 --> 01:36:42,164
She's donating everything
to the church.

908
01:36:42,651 --> 01:36:47,122
She works in the parish
and is going to volunteer in Africa.

909
01:36:47,411 --> 01:36:52,087
The trains at our parties
are the best ones in Rome!

910
01:36:52,931 --> 01:36:54,922
- You think so?
- I do.

911
01:36:56,451 --> 01:36:59,966
They're the best because
they go nowhere.

912
01:37:10,731 --> 01:37:13,086
- Well?
- It's wonderful, thank you.

913
01:37:13,211 --> 01:37:15,771
Come on, it's all gone.

914
01:37:15,891 --> 01:37:19,327
Tell me why you left me, please.

915
01:37:19,451 --> 01:37:21,760
I want an explanation, please!

916
01:37:22,611 --> 01:37:25,648
Go away!
Get out! Get out!

917
01:37:50,491 --> 01:37:52,322
You see all these people?

918
01:37:53,371 --> 01:37:55,362
They can't do anything.

919
01:37:55,931 --> 01:37:58,570
But I know how to do something.

920
01:37:59,331 --> 01:38:02,004
We know how to do something.

921
01:38:03,291 --> 01:38:05,043
How sweet!

922
01:38:47,411 --> 01:38:51,643
They've been asking me for years
why I don't write another novel.

923
01:38:52,811 --> 01:38:54,802
But look at these people.

924
01:38:55,811 --> 01:38:57,927
This wildlife!

925
01:38:58,891 --> 01:39:01,963
This is my life
and it's nothing.

926
01:39:05,251 --> 01:39:07,970
Flaubert wanted to write a book
about nothing but he failed,

927
01:39:08,091 --> 01:39:10,241
so could I do it?

928
01:39:16,931 --> 01:39:19,570
It's nice.
Thanks, rascal.

929
01:39:33,011 --> 01:39:35,241
What inspired this exhibition?

930
01:39:36,211 --> 01:39:39,328
It wasn't my idea
to do this photo exhibition.

931
01:39:39,451 --> 01:39:41,601
It was my father's idea.

932
01:39:42,451 --> 01:39:45,682
When I was born, he starting taking
photos of me, every day.

933
01:39:45,891 --> 01:39:47,768
One photo per day.

934
01:39:48,331 --> 01:39:50,640
He never forgot, not even once.

935
01:39:51,371 --> 01:39:55,046
From the age of 14 upwards,
I continued.

936
01:39:55,731 --> 01:39:58,848
I photographed myself every day.

937
01:40:03,131 --> 01:40:04,723
Go ahead.

938
01:41:44,131 --> 01:41:46,804
- Cardinal!
- Your Eminence!

939
01:41:49,811 --> 01:41:52,279
Cardinal,
when will The Saint arrive in Rome?

940
01:41:52,411 --> 01:41:55,687
On Thursday,
but please don't call her The Saint.

941
01:41:55,811 --> 01:41:59,804
She is a Saint but not technically.

942
01:42:00,731 --> 01:42:03,529
Tell me something,
who is that cardinal?

943
01:42:03,651 --> 01:42:05,960
- That's Bellucci.
- Bellucci?

944
01:42:06,091 --> 01:42:07,843
- The one in line to be...
- Exactly.

945
01:42:07,971 --> 01:42:09,962
The papal throne awaits him.

946
01:42:10,171 --> 01:42:12,765
I met him at Giada Ricci's
carnival party.

947
01:42:12,891 --> 01:42:16,008
Rumor has it that he used to be
Europe's best exorcist.

948
01:42:16,131 --> 01:42:17,849
- Are you pulling my leg?
- No.

949
01:42:18,691 --> 01:42:20,443
I never joke about the devil.

950
01:42:20,971 --> 01:42:24,168
Do you know I'm very, very bored.

951
01:42:25,451 --> 01:42:28,170
We're having a great, great time.

952
01:42:28,851 --> 01:42:30,569
You cut up the duck.

953
01:42:30,691 --> 01:42:35,845
Cook it on a high flame
for 15 minutes.

954
01:42:35,971 --> 01:42:37,643
At that point...

955
01:42:37,811 --> 01:42:40,609
Cardinal, do you remember me?
Lello Cava.

956
01:42:40,731 --> 01:42:44,644
We met at Giada Ricci's party.
I was dressed as an escort.

957
01:42:45,091 --> 01:42:47,605
Come, they're starting
to serve lunch.

958
01:42:47,891 --> 01:42:51,327
I'd like you meet my writer friend,
Jep Gambardella.

959
01:42:52,011 --> 01:42:56,448
A writer!
This country needs writers.

960
01:42:56,571 --> 01:42:58,687
Actually I thought it was more
in need of priests.

961
01:42:58,851 --> 01:42:59,647
Help.

962
01:42:59,771 --> 01:43:02,922
- May I ask you a question?
- Of course, my dear man.

963
01:43:03,051 --> 01:43:05,963
Well, for some time now...

964
01:43:11,651 --> 01:43:14,449
from a spiritual point of view...

965
01:43:15,451 --> 01:43:19,763
- Skunk hunt?
- Of course, I'll lead the way!

966
01:43:19,891 --> 01:43:23,122
I know the Tebaldi grounds well.

967
01:43:28,891 --> 01:43:33,009
Jep Gambardella, the king
of socialites! You're losing it.

968
01:43:33,131 --> 01:43:38,330
I've been losing it for 40 years.
It's a steady decline.

969
01:43:42,411 --> 01:43:47,963
Tell me something, Stefania.
Have we ever slept with each other?

970
01:43:48,691 --> 01:43:51,000
Of course not!

971
01:43:55,411 --> 01:43:59,563
That's an awfully big mistake!
We must make amends, immediately.

972
01:44:00,531 --> 01:44:02,522
Idiot.

973
01:44:05,091 --> 01:44:06,922
Thank goodness.

974
01:44:08,171 --> 01:44:11,243
We still have something nice
to do together.

975
01:44:14,171 --> 01:44:17,243
The future is marvelous, Stefania.

976
01:44:51,371 --> 01:44:54,283
To be honest, Catellani
hasn't had many brushed fabrics

977
01:44:54,411 --> 01:44:56,561
in recent years.

978
01:44:56,691 --> 01:44:59,967
In my opinion, Rebecchi's still
the best tailor in Rome.

979
01:45:03,451 --> 01:45:06,329
- Who are you?
- A hard-working man.

980
01:45:06,451 --> 01:45:11,241
One who, while you play the artist
and have fun with your friends,

981
01:45:11,371 --> 01:45:13,646
keeps this country going.

982
01:45:13,771 --> 01:45:16,365
I keep this country going,

983
01:45:16,491 --> 01:45:19,164
but many people
haven't understood that yet.

984
01:45:21,851 --> 01:45:26,367
Imagine that, Dadina,
Giulio Moneta was my neighbor.

985
01:45:26,491 --> 01:45:31,849
One of the world's 10 most wanted
men and I never noticed.

986
01:45:31,971 --> 01:45:34,724
You've changed,
you're always thinking.

987
01:45:37,171 --> 01:45:39,446
Maybe I should do what Romano did.

988
01:45:40,331 --> 01:45:42,526
I'm not fit for this life
or this city.

989
01:45:42,651 --> 01:45:47,122
Nobody's fit for shit, damnit.
Take it from the queen of misfits.

990
01:45:48,451 --> 01:45:50,919
Everything around me is dying.

991
01:45:51,891 --> 01:45:55,008
People who are younger than me,
things...

992
01:45:55,851 --> 01:45:57,045
All before my eyes and I...

993
01:45:57,171 --> 01:46:00,607
And you're suffering.
And you don't understand.

994
01:46:08,331 --> 01:46:10,765
How's the soup, Little Jep?

995
01:46:13,331 --> 01:46:15,049
The soup's good.

996
01:46:17,251 --> 01:46:21,085
Why did you call me Little Jep? No
one's called me that for centuries.

997
01:46:21,211 --> 01:46:23,486
Because a friend,
every now and again,

998
01:46:23,651 --> 01:46:27,087
needs to make their friend
feel like they did as a child.

999
01:46:29,051 --> 01:46:31,565
How can I make you feel
like a little girl?

1000
01:46:31,691 --> 01:46:34,524
You don't need to, I feel
like a little girl every day!

1001
01:46:34,651 --> 01:46:38,200
I've seen the world from
their viewpoint for 60 years.

1002
01:46:39,491 --> 01:46:41,641
You know Sister Maria,
the missionary,

1003
01:46:42,291 --> 01:46:43,770
the one they call the Saint?

1004
01:46:43,891 --> 01:46:47,725
Yes, she's coming to Rome
to receive some honor.

1005
01:46:47,851 --> 01:46:51,127
Exactly. In all her life,
she's only given three interviews.

1006
01:46:51,251 --> 01:46:54,766
- Yours will be memorable.
- Yeah sure, think of Giulio Moneta!

1007
01:46:54,891 --> 01:46:58,679
This is different.
She studied in Italy

1008
01:46:58,811 --> 01:47:01,723
and speaks Italian.
She read your book and loved it.

1009
01:47:02,331 --> 01:47:03,650
She wants to meet you

1010
01:47:03,771 --> 01:47:05,966
so I organized a dinner party
at your house tomorrow.

1011
01:47:06,091 --> 01:47:09,561
- Did I do well?
- You did very well.

1012
01:49:07,571 --> 01:49:11,246
Tomorrow I'll have the honor
of dining with her.

1013
01:49:11,371 --> 01:49:13,805
- At the Holy Father's?
- No.

1014
01:49:13,971 --> 01:49:15,484
No, at Jep Gambardella's.

1015
01:49:16,251 --> 01:49:22,008
You see, the Pope even invited
the enclosed nuns.

1016
01:49:55,771 --> 01:49:58,285
Sisters, sisters, sisters!

1017
01:49:59,211 --> 01:50:01,042
Sisters, sisters...
Yes, perfect!

1018
01:50:03,451 --> 01:50:05,760
Ah, the Red Cross nurses!
Well-toned!

1019
01:50:05,931 --> 01:50:08,729
Okay, great...
What handsome young men!

1020
01:50:09,251 --> 01:50:10,525
Great!

1021
01:50:11,091 --> 01:50:12,490
Let's go!

1022
01:50:16,171 --> 01:50:18,127
The Saint's assistant called me.

1023
01:50:18,251 --> 01:50:22,005
The Saint would like Count and
Countess Odescalchi to come too,

1024
01:50:22,131 --> 01:50:24,601
as they treated her like a sister
when she lived in Italy.

1025
01:50:24,730 --> 01:50:27,680
- Do you know them?
- Of course, but they are not in Rome.

1026
01:50:27,710 --> 01:50:31,060
All the nobles are in London,
at Philip's great-niece's wedding.

1027
01:50:31,131 --> 01:50:34,123
Let's call the Colonnas of Reggio.

1028
01:50:34,251 --> 01:50:36,048
The nobles for hire?
They're dead.

1029
01:50:36,931 --> 01:50:38,649
Nonsense, they're immortal.

1030
01:50:38,771 --> 01:50:42,286
The Saint won't even notice,
70 years have gone by!

1031
01:50:43,011 --> 01:50:45,081
This piece of furniture
looks great...

1032
01:50:45,251 --> 01:50:49,847
- Who would've thought!
- It looks great, like a new bathroom!

1033
01:50:54,291 --> 01:50:56,361
Count Colonna speaking.

1034
01:50:56,971 --> 01:50:59,280
Yes, we are available.

1035
01:51:00,191 --> 01:51:01,749
For tonight.

1036
01:51:02,151 --> 01:51:05,766
Our rate is 250 Euros per person
for the evening.

1037
01:51:06,291 --> 01:51:09,408
Plus the cost of the car hire.

1038
01:51:10,491 --> 01:51:14,928
This would be somewhat
humiliating for us...

1039
01:51:15,551 --> 01:51:20,308
We are willing to be hired
as the Colonnas of Reggio.

1040
01:51:20,731 --> 01:51:24,804
But as for pretending to be
the Odescalchis...

1041
01:51:25,171 --> 01:51:26,365
I don't know...

1042
01:51:27,651 --> 01:51:30,324
We were at war for two centuries.

1043
01:51:31,041 --> 01:51:32,838
I feel it's immoral.

1044
01:51:33,031 --> 01:51:37,229
Cut at least twelve pieces
of rabbit!

1045
01:51:37,791 --> 01:51:41,227
Set aside the kidneys, liver,
head...

1046
01:51:41,531 --> 01:51:43,408
Gently brown.

1047
01:51:44,250 --> 01:51:47,050
Don't forget thyme,
laurel leaves, rosemary...

1048
01:51:47,080 --> 01:51:51,278
Then red wine, Ligurian olives...
pine nuts.

1049
01:51:52,051 --> 01:51:55,009
And after an hour,
you have Ligurian-style rabbit!

1050
01:51:55,691 --> 01:51:58,000
Sister Maria, what convent
are you staying at?

1051
01:51:58,131 --> 01:52:01,919
Actually, we're at the Hassler Hotel
at the Spanish Steps.

1052
01:52:02,891 --> 01:52:05,785
To be honest, Sister Maria
finds it uncomfortable.

1053
01:52:05,860 --> 01:52:08,328
Never heard the Hassler
described as uncomfortable!

1054
01:52:08,691 --> 01:52:10,124
It's very comfortable

1055
01:52:10,251 --> 01:52:13,402
but Sister Maria isn't used
to sleeping in a bed.

1056
01:52:13,971 --> 01:52:17,088
She sleeps on the floor,
in a cardboard bed.

1057
01:52:17,170 --> 01:52:19,161
Do you have any visits planned?

1058
01:52:19,331 --> 01:52:21,162
Sister Maria will climb

1059
01:52:21,240 --> 01:52:23,390
St John's Basilica's Scala Sancta
on her knees.

1060
01:52:23,731 --> 01:52:26,245
- Have you?
- I'd have liked to, but...

1061
01:52:26,371 --> 01:52:29,204
I have a bad knee...

1062
01:52:29,331 --> 01:52:31,799
Orthopedic problems
are unimportant,

1063
01:52:32,011 --> 01:52:36,607
compared to the partial indulgence
granted by the Scala Sancta.

1064
01:52:36,731 --> 01:52:41,247
That's true! Another specialty
of mine is lamb with...

1065
01:52:41,371 --> 01:52:44,329
Does Sister Maria still help
the sick?

1066
01:52:44,611 --> 01:52:47,569
22 hours a day, every day.

1067
01:52:47,731 --> 01:52:51,087
She washes them, feeds them...
You ought to see her.

1068
01:52:51,251 --> 01:52:53,719
Despite her age,
she doesn't walk, she runs.

1069
01:52:53,851 --> 01:52:59,847
Now she's tired, but that's because
she's not with her patients.

1070
01:53:00,011 --> 01:53:01,524
How old is she?

1071
01:53:01,651 --> 01:53:03,562
She'll be 104 in October.

1072
01:53:03,731 --> 01:53:05,881
- That's impressive.
- I thought she was older!

1073
01:53:06,051 --> 01:53:10,806
Longevity too, like all things,
is not accidental.

1074
01:53:10,971 --> 01:53:13,485
About Sister Maria's interview
with Jep...

1075
01:53:13,611 --> 01:53:18,560
Her interview?
There must be a mix-up...

1076
01:53:18,691 --> 01:53:21,489
Sister Maria hasn't given
any interviews since 1971,

1077
01:53:21,611 --> 01:53:24,250
after the reason
for her mission in Chad,

1078
01:53:24,371 --> 01:53:27,010
was misunderstood by some.

1079
01:53:27,491 --> 01:53:30,483
Of course, but considering
her admiration for Jep's work...

1080
01:53:30,651 --> 01:53:32,926
You told me she enjoyed
"The Human Apparatus".

1081
01:53:33,091 --> 01:53:36,208
She found it beautiful and fierce.

1082
01:53:36,331 --> 01:53:38,242
Like the world of men.

1083
01:53:38,371 --> 01:53:40,965
Great! There would be no risk
of any misunderstanding,

1084
01:53:41,131 --> 01:53:42,962
Sister Maria can review the text...

1085
01:53:43,171 --> 01:53:46,163
- No, I'm sorry.
- Don't insist.

1086
01:53:46,331 --> 01:53:49,607
I don't wish to raise
any false hopes,

1087
01:53:49,731 --> 01:53:53,167
there's absolutely
no question of any interview.

1088
01:53:53,291 --> 01:53:56,124
Sorry, but why do
you always answer?

1089
01:53:56,251 --> 01:53:58,287
Why not let Sister Maria talk?

1090
01:54:16,731 --> 01:54:19,040
Madam...

1091
01:54:21,731 --> 01:54:25,724
I took a vow of poverty.

1092
01:54:27,491 --> 01:54:31,803
And you can't talk about poverty...

1093
01:54:33,451 --> 01:54:35,123
you have to live it.

1094
01:54:46,011 --> 01:54:49,845
Such true and real words!
Powerful words!

1095
01:54:53,811 --> 01:54:55,802
Do you need anything, madam?

1096
01:54:56,451 --> 01:54:58,726
- She needs the bathroom.
- It's on the left.

1097
01:54:58,891 --> 01:55:01,564
The change of diet
isn't good for her.

1098
01:55:01,691 --> 01:55:07,880
Sister Maria, in Mali, only eats
40 grams of plant roots a day.

1099
01:55:08,171 --> 01:55:11,447
Me too sometimes, in the evening,
as a light meal,

1100
01:55:11,571 --> 01:55:15,007
I have some splendid
roots with lemon.

1101
01:55:15,131 --> 01:55:18,248
You clean the roots
by scraping them with a knife

1102
01:55:18,451 --> 01:55:21,761
and you cut them into small
chunks...

1103
01:55:21,971 --> 01:55:25,168
Cardinal, remember when we met
at that wedding?

1104
01:55:25,371 --> 01:55:27,043
You were there too...

1105
01:55:28,531 --> 01:55:33,559
I felt the need to ask you
about matters close to my heart.

1106
01:55:33,811 --> 01:55:36,279
Matters regarding faith...

1107
01:55:36,611 --> 01:55:40,286
regarding the strength
of spirituality...

1108
01:55:40,611 --> 01:55:42,602
But then you got distracted.

1109
01:55:42,771 --> 01:55:44,170
You can ask me now.

1110
01:55:46,051 --> 01:55:49,600
- No, I don't see the point.
- Why?

1111
01:55:49,731 --> 01:55:55,328
I'd be very disappointed to discover
that you have no answers.

1112
01:55:55,811 --> 01:55:58,405
I'm only saying
it's a possibility...

1113
01:55:58,531 --> 01:56:00,408
I think that...

1114
01:56:06,571 --> 01:56:07,686
Never mind...

1115
01:56:12,971 --> 01:56:14,609
I apologize for earlier.

1116
01:56:14,811 --> 01:56:18,326
There is one question
I really want to ask you.

1117
01:56:19,411 --> 01:56:21,971
Are the rumors about you true?

1118
01:56:23,011 --> 01:56:24,888
That you were a truly great...

1119
01:56:26,931 --> 01:56:28,603
exorcist?

1120
01:56:56,451 --> 01:56:58,282
Sister Maria...

1121
01:56:58,811 --> 01:57:00,290
Sister Maria!

1122
01:57:02,251 --> 01:57:03,809
- Sister Maria!
- Saint...

1123
01:57:03,931 --> 01:57:05,762
- Have you seen her?
- No, she's not there.

1124
01:57:08,131 --> 01:57:09,849
- Sister Maria!
- Saint...

1125
01:57:09,971 --> 01:57:11,199
Sister Maria!

1126
01:57:11,331 --> 01:57:12,366
Saint!

1127
01:57:12,491 --> 01:57:15,164
She's called Sister Maria.

1128
01:57:15,291 --> 01:57:16,929
Sister Maria...

1129
01:57:17,051 --> 01:57:19,849
Where has that bitch got to?

1130
01:57:43,891 --> 01:57:45,722
Sister Maria!

1131
01:57:48,531 --> 01:57:50,487
Sister Maria!

1132
01:57:52,931 --> 01:57:54,284
My goodness!

1133
01:57:55,651 --> 01:57:57,403
My goodness!

1134
01:58:28,451 --> 01:58:31,284
Come, Elisabetta, let's go to bed.

1135
01:58:31,451 --> 01:58:34,329
You go ahead, I'm going upstairs
for a moment.

1136
01:58:35,571 --> 01:58:37,641
Don't be late.

1137
01:59:49,211 --> 01:59:52,009
In this room, in 1930,

1138
01:59:52,131 --> 01:59:55,521
Princess Antonietta gave birth
to her only daughter,

1139
01:59:55,651 --> 01:59:57,846
Elisabetta Colonna of Reggio.

1140
01:59:58,211 --> 02:00:01,248
The princess died
after giving birth.

1141
02:00:01,371 --> 02:00:04,249
Young Elisabetta,
in these opulent rooms,

1142
02:00:04,371 --> 02:00:07,124
had a happy and carefree
childhood.

1143
02:00:07,251 --> 02:00:11,961
But shortly after, the financial
hardship endured by Prince Erminio,

1144
02:00:12,571 --> 02:00:15,324
forced him to sell the property.

1145
02:00:50,771 --> 02:00:52,807
They're migrating west...

1146
02:00:52,971 --> 02:00:56,884
but now they are resting.

1147
02:01:10,171 --> 02:01:11,809
Did you know

1148
02:01:12,731 --> 02:01:17,009
that I know the Christian names...

1149
02:01:17,611 --> 02:01:21,570
of all of these birds?

1150
02:01:28,971 --> 02:01:30,086
Why...

1151
02:01:31,851 --> 02:01:35,287
did you never write another book?

1152
02:01:41,451 --> 02:01:43,203
I was looking for the great beauty,

1153
02:01:45,291 --> 02:01:46,929
but...

1154
02:01:50,051 --> 02:01:51,245
I didn't find it.

1155
02:01:53,091 --> 02:01:54,809
Do you know...

1156
02:01:55,611 --> 02:01:57,124
why...

1157
02:01:57,811 --> 02:02:00,723
I only eat roots?

1158
02:02:06,051 --> 02:02:07,643
No, why?

1159
02:02:14,571 --> 02:02:18,962
Because roots are important.

1160
02:04:48,131 --> 02:04:51,885
Now there's something
I want to show you.

1161
02:05:50,731 --> 02:05:54,201
This is how it always ends.
With death.

1162
02:05:55,411 --> 02:05:58,642
But first there was life.

1163
02:05:59,131 --> 02:06:03,010
Hidden beneath the blah, blah, blah.

1164
02:06:05,371 --> 02:06:10,126
It is all settled beneath
the chitter chatter and the noise.

1165
02:06:10,931 --> 02:06:14,287
Silence and sentiment.

1166
02:06:14,771 --> 02:06:17,763
Emotion and fear.

1167
02:06:18,971 --> 02:06:24,284
The haggard, inconstant
flashes of beauty.

1168
02:06:25,011 --> 02:06:30,085
And then the wretched squalor
and miserable humanity.

1169
02:06:31,211 --> 02:06:35,602
All buried under the cover of the
embarrassment of being in the world.

1170
02:06:40,811 --> 02:06:44,326
Beyond there,
is what lies beyond.

1171
02:06:45,331 --> 02:06:48,721
I don't deal
with what lies beyond.

1172
02:06:49,811 --> 02:06:54,601
Therefore...
let this novel begin.

1173
02:06:55,451 --> 02:06:59,285
After all...
it's just a trick.

1174
02:07:00,251 --> 02:07:03,926
Yes, it's just a trick.

